From c3823124bc92658ad4226754ae864963fb2bb016 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: =?UTF-8?q?Witold=20Bo=C5=82t?= <witold.bolt@jit.team>
Date: Fri, 26 Jun 2026 21:55:50 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 12/17] v3dv: force DISABLE_TFU on Phoenix (winsys has no
 SUBMIT_TFU ioctl -> textures black)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

ROOT CAUSE of "every sampled texture renders black on the Pi4 V3D" (notex draws fine,
all textured draws black, descriptors+samplers valid, persistent across frames): the
Phoenix no-WSI fb0 winsys (v3d_phoenix_winsys.c) implements only DRM_V3D_SUBMIT_CL; its
ioctl dispatch ends `default: return 0`, so DRM_V3D_SUBMIT_TFU is a SILENT no-op that
returns success. V3DV prefers the TFU for buffer<->image / image<->image copies, blits,
and mipmap-gen of tiled (OPTIMAL) images — and all sampled textures here are
VK_IMAGE_TILING_OPTIMAL (gl_texmgr.c:1035) — so every texture upload was submitted as a
TFU job that never executed; the dst image stayed at its winsys alloc-time zero -> texels
sample 0 -> black. (The linear fb0 scanout never uses TFU, which is why the notex/clear
path renders.)

Fix: force V3D_DEBUG_DISABLE_TFU under __phoenix__ right after v3d_process_debug_variable().
DISABLE_TFU is an upstream-supported debug mode, so a non-TFU CL fallback (copy_*_tlb /
blit_shader, submitted via DRM_V3D_SUBMIT_CL — the path the winsys DOES execute) is
guaranteed for every TFU operation. This is correctness on this winsys, not perf;
implementing ioc_submit_tfu in the winsys is a future optimization (TODO noted in source).
A one-time stderr marker ("DISABLE_TFU forced") proves the running binary carries it (no
string otherwise — it's a numeric OR) and serves as the mesa-layer pre-boot gate.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 src/broadcom/vulkan/v3dv_device.c | 18 ++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 18 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/broadcom/vulkan/v3dv_device.c b/src/broadcom/vulkan/v3dv_device.c
index 97baf74e608..199c9c27123 100644
--- a/src/broadcom/vulkan/v3dv_device.c
+++ b/src/broadcom/vulkan/v3dv_device.c
@@ -693,6 +693,24 @@ v3dv_CreateInstance(const VkInstanceCreateInfo *pCreateInfo,
 
    v3d_process_debug_variable();
 
+#if defined(__phoenix__)
+   /* Phoenix no-WSI fb0 winsys does not implement the DRM_V3D_SUBMIT_TFU ioctl (its
+    * ioctl dispatch handles only DRM_V3D_SUBMIT_CL; everything else is a silent no-op
+    * `default: return 0`). The TFU is V3DV's *preferred* (faster) path for buffer<->image
+    * and image<->image copies, blits, and mipmap generation of tiled/OPTIMAL images, so on
+    * this port every such copy was submitted as a TFU job that never executed -> the
+    * destination image stayed at its alloc-time zero -> every sampled texture rendered
+    * BLACK (root-caused: notex draws fine, all textured draws black, descriptors/samplers
+    * valid). Forcing DISABLE_TFU routes ALL of those operations to the CL fallback
+    * (copy_*_tlb / blit_shader), which submits through DRM_V3D_SUBMIT_CL — the path the
+    * winsys does execute. DISABLE_TFU is an upstream-supported debug mode, so a non-TFU CL
+    * fallback is guaranteed for every TFU path. This is correctness (not perf) on this
+    * winsys; implementing the TFU submit is a future optimization.
+    * TODO(vkquake-port): drop once ioc_submit_tfu is implemented in v3d_phoenix_winsys.c. */
+   v3d_mesa_debug |= V3D_DEBUG_DISABLE_TFU;
+   fprintf(stderr, "v3dv: Phoenix DISABLE_TFU forced (no-WSI winsys, CL copy fallback)\n");
+#endif
+
    instance->vk.physical_devices.enumerate = enumerate_devices;
    instance->vk.physical_devices.destroy = destroy_physical_device;
 
